reviews.text:
Stopped by Urban Thai for dinner with friends. Dada is super friendly and lovely! It exceeded all my expectations and delivered great Thai dining experience.
Their menu is extensive, with focus on southern Thai cuisine which is known for its bold and complex flavors. The service was quick and friendly. We ordered pad thai, beef curry, stir fry....and everything was good!

reviews.text: I really wanted to like Calico. Good food - if not inspired - and friendly and helpful staff. But we sat for 20 mins after arrival with no water as the place seemed VERY short of staff for a busy Saturday lunch, and our second drinks order never actually appeared by the time we had finished our meals. Big portions of interesting food and a lively environment were pluses.

reviews.text: Best thai spot in Zetland! Cozy restaurant with authentic and delicious food. The ambience is very welcoming too. Ordered the recommended Khao Soi and it was great for the rainy weather. Nasi goreng was tasty too but on the spicer side (our fault as this is mentioned on the menu)

reviews.text:
We had a great experience and Jackson treated us handsomely. The eggplant was the highlight, really , really good, crispy, smoky, flavourful. The pork chops were also very good.

The dumplings and the blood sausage werenâ€™t impressive. The cod roe was really interesting.

While it was good, for that price point and level of hype I was expecting something really impressive, and it wasnâ€™t necessarily that. The kitchen was slow at times with weird waiting times between dishes and then several coming at once. The food was very good but save the eggplant nothing really blew my mind.

name: NOUR
address: Middle Eastern Â· î¤´ Â· 3/490 Crown St
details: Chic eatery with inventive Lebanese fare

reviews.text: I'm getting the feeling that this place is a birthday destination; every table around us got their birthday treat from the restaurant, and ours wasn't the exception. The food was lovely, the atmosphere was lovely and the service was excellent. I'm not going to say it had the best food in town, it didn't, but it was good and we all enjoyed it. Parking is tricky, and if not on a weekend, i can only imagine it to be harder. Allow plenty of extra time to organise parking if you're driving there. Here's a random piece of info, their toilets are nice and clean, however, for some reason, their cubicles have prison grade doors! Very weird, I'm not sure if they are designed to keep people in or out! I put a photo for you to judge for yourself ðŸ¤” All in all it's worth the visit. And of course, expect to pay for the privilege.

Wow. What a hidden treasure- garlic prawns were fantastic.

Family run.
